      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "b47f65bc080c2957",
      "text": "The interpersonal dynamics within any classroom or school building are complex. There is often a lot of energy spent just keeping focus so that a learning experience doesn’t feel like it is spinning out of control. When you are focused on managing this complexity, it is difficult to listen to the different voices in the room. You sense, however, that there are important insights from a new learning experience, particularly when you are seeking to fulfill your commitment to equity.\n"
    },
